An additional $1,000 is also budgeted for any additional hardware costs associated with the project, including the purchase of extra hard drives to store the backups of the websites.
At a cost of $12/hour, over the course of 3 weeks, our 3 student employees will take 120 hours to create the manuals. The total cost of this phase will be 120 x 12 = $1440 dollars.
Plugins should all be compatible with the current version of WordPress.  There is a risk that users may upgrade their WordPress accounts before testing of the plugins can be done on newer versions.
The tutorial may be difficult to follow for non-technical users.  We plan to mitigate this risk by making sure the tutorials contain simple step-by-step methods with pictures and videos.
